<B> ABOUT </B>

<p align='justify'> 360 Degree Private Limited is an ISO 9001:2015 certified, Ministry of Tourism - Govt of
 India & Directorate of Tourism – West Bengal Govt approved Travel House. Company is member
 of PATA – India Chapter, IATO-Indian Association of Tour Operators, 
 ATOAI-Adventure Tour Operators Association of India, TAAB-Travel Agent Association 
 of Bengal & EHTTOA-Eastern Himalaya Travel & Tour Operators Association.
 Incredible India and Beautiful Bengal is a rare combination of nature, culture and architectural
 wonders. Denzong Leisure aims to introduce you to these wonderful, hidden, natural
 treasures with a touch of ever desired premium support and services.</p>

<p>Company has been awarded "The Best Leisure Product" in TTF, New Delhi - 2016
Company has been awarded "Most Promising New Destination" in TTF, Kolkata - 2018</p>

<p> <b> WE ARE MORE THAN A TRAVEL COMPANY </b></p>

<p align='justify'>We are the complete DMC – (Destination Management Company), we don’t just sale
 – we provide free Travel Consultancy and make you choose the best. We are the
 provider of a complete package of services in the field of Travel & Tourism, 
 starting from Flight / Helicopter / Car / Bus / Cruise booking to Jungle Safaris, 
 Beach Holidays, Mountain Tourism, Honeymoon special packages, Adventure Tourism,
 Bird Watching, MICE Tours and River Tourism. We provide our guests with customized
 travel solutions that cater to specific needs. We serve with a smile ensuring your
 contentment.</p>

<p> <b> OUR VISION </b></p>

<p align='justify' > Promoting Incredible India and Beautiful Bengal, our primary objective is to actively 
encourage eco-friendly and responsible tourism. Focus areas are West Bengal, North Eastern 
States and the Neighboring Countries.We are striving to be one of the leading, process-driven
 DMCs based out of Eastern India. The company focuses on maximizing the employment opportunity
 for the local community and is dedicated to the conservation of natural resources and the local
 culture of these regions.</p>




